Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome: update, 16 Mar 2000 20000319.0380
[1
Date: Fri, 25 Aug 2000 00:22:53 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: The Albuquerque Journal. Associated Press, filed 24 Aug 2000 [edited

Hantavirus, pulmonary syndrome - USA (New Mexico)
-------------------------------------------------
A McKinley County man has been diagnosed with a hantavirus infection - the
10th person to contract the disease this year in New Mexico, officials
said. The unidentified 49-year-old man was listed in critical condition on
Thu 24 Aug 2000 at University Hospital in Albuquerque. Eight of the 10
hantavirus infections this year have been diagnosed as the often fatal
hantavirus pulmonary syndrome, while 2 of them had lesser infections.
"Nine of the 10 total number of hantavirus infections this year have been
from McKinley County. This number of cases in one county is cause for
concern," said state epidemiologist Dr. Paul Ettestad.
--
[It is presumed that Sin Nombre virus is the hantavirus responsible for
these illnesses, in 8 of the 10 cases at least, but the report does not
confirm this. - Mod.CP
